results.name: Quotient of n over the maximum divisor of n whose prime multiplicities are distinct.
comment: A number's prime multiplicities are also called its (unsorted) prime signature.
link: Gus Wiseman, Sequences counting and encoding certain classes of multisets
example: The maximum such divisor of 60 is 20, so a(60) = 3.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 16 2019
